cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on word embeddings, which are commonly used in NLP systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new approach for learning word sense embeddings, which involves using word sense definitions. This approach involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on word similarity tasks and word sense disambiguation, which could fall under categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
